lead_paragraph: OUR CANADIAN GUESTS have mostly left the city for their homes. A very few, however, yet remain for the purpose of seeing all the "notions" and other matters of interest about our city. Yesterday, a party of architects and engineers from Toronto, visited the station-houses of the various railways in the city.
